text: Enoch Train (1801–1868) was an American shipowner and merchant. Enoch Train may also refer to: ==Vessels== * CSS Manassas, originally named Enoch Train, an 1855 twin-screw towboat * SS Enoch Train, a Liberty ship built in 1943 and scrapped in 1966 ==Other uses== * Enoch Train (band), an American folk/world music band
title: Enoch Train (disambiguation)
